read_metric(25.10)                                          read_metric(25.10)

Name  read_metric - Loads a previously saved metric file for querying, report-
       ing, and comparing
Syntax
Parameters -help Outputs a brief description that includes  type  and  default
       information  for each read_metric parameter. For a detailed description
       of the command and all of its parameters,  use  the  man  command:  man
       read_metric  -id< snapshotName > Specifies the name of snapshot to cre-
       ate or overwrite. Data_type: string, optional  <metricsFile>  Specifies
       the name of the metrics file. Data_type: string, required -merge Merges
       the  metrics  into the named snapshot, instead of replacing. Data_type:
       bool, optional -previous <UniqueID>  Specifies  the  uuid  of  previous
       snapshots for the new pending snapshot. Data_type: string, optional
